  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-03 stale input data)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. A model revision was issued on 2025-11-14 to update the impeller blade-angle parameterisation; the primary experimental dataset carries a dataVintage of 2025-10-22, predating that revision. The assessment team judged the geometric change not material to the hemolysis scalar QoI and did not commission a formal re-validation against post-revision geometry, leaving an unresolved epistemic gap. Decision recorded as Accepted on the basis of the team's undocumented engineering judgement.",
