    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The assessment team accepted the model for VAD hemolysis prediction based on the overall Monte Carlo UQ results and the 18% NIH agreement across 5 operating points. The model revision of 2025-11-14 (blade-angle parameterisation update) was judged by the team to be not material to the hemolysis scalar QoI, citing a prior parametric sweep showing less than 2% NIH sensitivity to blade-angle variations in the pre-revision geometry. Consequently, no formal re-validation against post-revision geometry was commissioned and the primary experimental dataset (dataVintage 2025-10-22) was retained as current evidence. Multiple credibility factors remain below required levels and six factors were not assessed; however, the team accepted residual risk under schedule constraints for the regulatory submission window.",
